           <div class="caption offset2">
                    <h3>Coming Soon: Reformatting and sculpting your data</h3>
                    <p>You will often find that governments, when releasing their data - will opt for a layout which looks visually pleasing to the human eye, but not make any sense to a computer. Your computer doesn't care about bold formatting - lines and blank rows and columns that make spreadsheets visually more appealing. In fact, they can often confuse matters. </p>
                  </div>
